    <note>Zeng(1) Yizhan [7363] Ancestors were probably Luguo Zeng(1), but moved to Nanchang during Wang Mang's interregnum (see documentation for ancestor, Ketu [16575]). Zhao's [7072], Gong's [7364] and Bu's [1707] father, Yi(2)'s [1704], Yu's [1712], Yu(2)'s [1713], Xu's [7073] and Xun's [7362] grandfather, Wang(2) Jizhi(2)'s [7369], Wang(2) Jixing's [7370], and Wang(2) Wujiu's [7384] (twice: sororate) father-in-law. A nephew, Fou [3903], was appointed Kuizhou yunpan and concurrently Tiju in 1073, but was dismissed because the laws of avoidance precluded his serving as Tiju when his cousin, Bu, [1707] was Tongpan Sinong si. XCB, 243.9a-9b, 244.11b, 245.1a, 246.13b; Zeng Gong, WJ, 46.2b, 11a, 12a, 12b; Zou Hao, WJ, 37.7b; Wang Anshi, WJ, 93.959-961, 100.1030 (wife, born Wu(3), a Fuzhou, Linchuan resident, who married him at age 14 and died at age 35 after having given birth to Yizhan's #2 son, Gong, and #3-4 sons, Mou [16580] and Zai [16581]); Chen Shidao, WJ, 16.10b-11b (notes second wife, n??? Zhu(1)). CBD, 4, 2827-8.</note>
